__NOTOC__ {{Infobox ancient site |name = Camarata |native_name = |alternate_name = |image = |image_size = 250px |alt = |caption = |map_type = Algeria |map_alt = |map_size = 250 |location = [[Sidi Djeloul]] |region = [[Sidi Safi]], [[A√Øn T√©mouchent Province|A√Øn T√©mouchent]], [[Algeria]] |coordinates = {{coord|35|21|16|N|1|17|14|W|display=inline,title}} |type = |part_of = |length = |width = |area = |height = |builder = |material = |built = |abandoned = |epochs = |cultures = |dependency_of = |occupants = |event = |excavations = |archaeologists = |condition = |ownership = |management = |public_access = |website = |notes = }}
'''Camarata''' ({{lang-xpu|ê§ä‚Ä¨ê§å‚Ä¨ê§Ä‚Ä¨}}, {{sc|km æ}}){{sfnp|Head & al.|p=889}}<ref name=h>{{harvp|Huss|1985|p=[https://books.google.co.kr/books?id=NvEK7kc3qnQC&pg=PA561 561]}}.</ref> was a [[Carthaginian Empire|Carthaginian]] and [[Roman Empire|Roman]] port on the [[Mediterranean]] near [[Siga]] in [[Mauretania]]. Under the Romans, it was part of the [[Roman province|province]] of [[Mauretania Caesariensis]]. Its ruins are thought to be those at the mouth of the [[Wadi Ghazer]]<ref>{{citation |last=De Graauw |first=Arthur |date=2018 |contribution=North Africa |contribution-url=https://www.ancientportsantiques.com/the-catalogue/north-africa/ |title=Ancient Ports |location=Grenoble |publisher= }}.</ref> at [[Sidi Djeloul]] in [[Sidi Safi]], [[Algeria]].<ref name=b>{{citation |title=Barrington Atlas |date=2000 |contribution=Camarata |contribution-url=https://www.trismegistos.org/place/36491 |publisher= |location= |author= |editor= }}.</ref>
==History== Camarata released [[bronze]] coins stamped with the town's [[Punic language|Punic]] name and a crudely-done head [[obverse]] and [[grape]]s and an ear of [[wheat]] [[obverse|reverse]].{{sfnp|Head & al.|p=889}}
After the [[French conquest of Algeria|French occupation]] of [[French Algeria|Algeria]], the area around Camarata became known for its high-quality [[iron ore]].{{sfnp|Playfair|1878|p=[https://archive.org/details/handbookfortrav19firgoog/page/n274 274]}}
