{{Infobox protected area | name = Chiang Dao Wildlife Sanctuary | alt_name = ‡πÄ‡∏Ç‡∏ï‡∏£‡∏±‡∏Å‡∏©‡∏≤‡∏û‡∏±‡∏ô‡∏ò‡∏∏‡πå‡∏™‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏ß‡πå‡∏õ‡πà‡∏≤‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß | iucn_category = Ia | photo = ChiangDao Mountains.JPG | photo_caption = [[Doi Chiang Dao]] is the highest peak in the sanctuary. | map = Thailand | map_caption = Location in [[Thailand]] | map_width = | location = [[Chiang Dao District|Chiang Dao]] and [[Wiang Haeng District|Wiang Haeng]] districts, [[Chiang Mai Province]] | nearest_city = | coordinates = {{coords|19|24|16.078|N|98|55|24.718|E|region:TH|display=inline, title}} | area = 521 km¬≤<ref name="Division of Information System">{{cite web |url=http://www.dnp.go.th/wildlife_it/n_web/menu_map/page_cd.php|title=‡πÄ‡∏Ç‡∏ï‡∏£‡∏±‡∏Å‡∏©‡∏≤‡∏û‡∏±‡∏ô‡∏ò‡∏∏‡πå‡∏™‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏ß‡πå‡∏õ‡πà‡∏≤‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß|author=Division of Information System on Wildlife Conservation. Wildlife Conservation Office. Department of National Parks, Wildlife and Plant Conservation|date=n.d. |access-date=14 July 2016 |language=Thai |trans-title=Chiang Dao Wildlife Sanctuary}}</ref> | established = 25 August 1978<ref>{{cite journal|journal=Royal Gazette|volume=95|issue=87 ‡∏â‡∏ö‡∏±‡∏ö‡∏û‡∏¥‡πÄ‡∏®‡∏©|pages=19‚Äì20|script-title=th:‡∏û‡∏£‡∏∞‡∏£‡∏≤‡∏ä‡∏Å‡∏§‡∏©‡∏é‡∏µ‡∏Å‡∏≤‡∏Å‡∏≥‡∏´‡∏ô‡∏î‡∏ö‡∏£‡∏¥‡πÄ‡∏ß‡∏ì‡∏ó‡∏µ‡πà‡∏î‡∏¥‡∏ô‡∏õ‡πà‡∏≤‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß ‡πÉ‡∏ô‡∏ó‡πâ‡∏≠‡∏á‡∏ó‡∏µ‡πà‡∏ï‡∏≥‡∏ö‡∏•‡πÄ‡∏°‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏á‡πÅ‡∏´‡∏á ‡∏ï‡∏≥‡∏ö‡∏•‡πÄ‡∏°‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏á‡∏á‡∏≤‡∏¢ ‡∏ï‡∏≥‡∏ö‡∏•‡πÄ‡∏°‡∏∑‡∏≠‡∏á‡∏Ñ‡∏≠‡∏á ‡∏ï‡∏≥‡∏ö‡∏•‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß ‡πÅ‡∏•‡∏∞‡∏ï‡∏≥‡∏ö‡∏•‡πÅ‡∏°‡πà‡∏ô‡∏∞ ‡∏≠‡∏≥‡πÄ‡∏†‡∏≠‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß ‡∏à‡∏±‡∏á‡∏´‡∏ß‡∏±‡∏î‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡πÉ‡∏´‡∏°‡πà ‡πÉ‡∏´‡πâ‡πÄ‡∏õ‡πá‡∏ô‡πÄ‡∏Ç‡∏ï‡∏£‡∏±‡∏Å‡∏©‡∏≤‡∏û‡∏±‡∏ô‡∏ò‡∏∏‡πå‡∏™‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏ß‡πå‡∏õ‡πà‡∏≤ ‡∏û.‡∏®. ‡πí‡πï‡πí‡πë|url=http://www.ratchakitcha.soc.go.th/DATA/PDF/2521/A/087/19.PDF|date=1978-08-24|language=Thai}}</ref> | visitation_num = | visitation_year = | governing_body = Wildlife Conservation Office }}
'''Chiang Dao Wildlife Sanctuary''' ({{lang-th|‡πÄ‡∏Ç‡∏ï‡∏£‡∏±‡∏Å‡∏©‡∏≤‡∏û‡∏±‡∏ô‡∏ò‡∏∏‡πå‡∏™‡∏±‡∏ï‡∏ß‡πå‡∏õ‡πà‡∏≤‡πÄ‡∏ä‡∏µ‡∏¢‡∏á‡∏î‡∏≤‡∏ß}}) is a protected area in [[Chiang Mai Province]], [[Thailand]]. Established on 25 August 1978, the sanctuary covers 521&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> of the [[Doi Chiang Dao]] and southern mountainous areas of the [[Daen Lao Range]], north of the [[Thanon Thong Chai Range]]. The tallest summit is 2,175 m high Doi Chiang Dao.
The sanctuary area is covered by various forest types, depending on altitude, including [[dry evergreen forest]]s, [[hill evergreen forest]]s, [[coniferous forests]], deciduous [[dipterocarp]] forests, and [[meadows]]. It is the home to a number of endangered species of animals, such as [[long-tailed goral]]s (''Naemorhedus caudatus''), [[Sumatran serow]]s (''Capricornis sumatraensis''), [[Asian golden cat]]s (''Catopuma temminckii''), and [[big-headed turtle]]s (''Platysternon megacephalum'').<ref name="Division of Information System"/> [[rufous-fronted babbler|Deignan's babblers]] (''Stachyridopsis rodolphei'') and ''[[Huia melasma]]'' are endemic to this area.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.norththailandbirding.com/pages/finder/endemics.html|title=Endemics|author=NorthThailandBirding.com|date=n.d.|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=IUCN>{{Cite journal | author = Stuart, S. | title = ''Huia melasma'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 2006 | page = e.T61865A12568334 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 2006 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/61865/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2006.RLTS.T61865A12568334.en | access-date = 13 January 2018}}</ref>
[[File:Cyornis banyumas.jpg|thumb|left|A photo of a [[hill blue flycatcher]] in the wildlife sanctuary.]]{{clear}}
