* 17 BCE - [[Baekje]], [[Wiryeseong|Wirye-seong]], settled. * 392 - [[Goguryeo]] in power. * 551 - [[Silla]]-Baekje alliance in power. * 1104 - [[Sukjong of Goryeo]] builds palace.
==14th-18th century==
* 1394 ** Capital of the [[Joseon Dynasty]] relocates to Seoul from [[Kaesong]].<ref name=brit1910-korea /> ** [[Jongmyo]] (shrine) built. * 1395 ** [[Gyeongbokgung|Gyeongbokgung Palace]] built. ** [[Jogyesa]] temple established. * 1396 - [[Fortress Wall of Seoul|Fortress Wall]] construction begins. * 1398 ** [[The Eight Gates of Seoul|Eight Gates]] built. ** [[Sungkyunkwan]] founded. * 1412 - [[Changdeokgung|Changdeokgung Palace]] built. * 1414 - [[Namdaemun Market]] active.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} * 1447 - [[Namdaemun]] rebuilt. * 1467 - [[Wongaksa Pagoda]] constructed. * 1592 - April: City [[Japanese invasions of Korea (1592‚Äì1598)|taken]] by Japanese forces.<ref name=brit1910-korea />
==18th-19th century== * 1711 - [[Donuimun]] and [[Gwanghuimun]] (gates) rebuilt. * 1741 - [[Changuimun]] (gate) rebuilt. * 1796 - [[Hwaseong Fortress]] built. * 1867 - [[Gwanghwamun]] (gate) reconstructed. * 1897 ** ''Kurisudo sinmun'' newspaper begins publication.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.worldcat.org/search?q=su%3ASeoul+%28Korea%29+Newspapers.&qt=hot_subject |location=USA |title=WorldCat |publisher=[[Online Computer Library Center]] |accessdate=12 February 2013}}</ref> ** [[Independence Gate]] erected. * 1898 - [[Myeongdong Cathedral]] consecrated. * 1899 - [[Kyunggi High School|Gwallim Middle School]] established. * 1900 ** Gyeongseong Station opens. ** [[Incheon]]-Seoul and [[Chemulpo]]-Seoul railways begin operating.<ref name=brit1910-korea>{{Citation |publisher = Encyclop√¶dia Britannica |publication-place = New York |title = The Encyclop√¶dia Britannica |publication-date = 1910 |oclc = 14782424 |edition=11th |chapterurl = https://archive.org/stream/encyclopaediabri15chisrich#page/908/mode/2up |chapter =Korea }}</ref>{{sfn|Hunter|1977}}
==20th century== ===1900s-1950s=== * 1901 ‚Äì [[Busan]]-Seoul railway begins operating.{{sfn|Hunter|1977}} * 1905 ** [[Uiju County|Uiju]]-Seoul railway begins operating.<ref name=brit1910-korea /> ** [[Dongdaemun Market]] in business.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} * 1906 ‚Äì ''[[Keij≈ç Nipp≈ç]]'' newspaper established.{{sfn|Henry|2005}} * 1907 ‚Äì Seoul Sanitation Association founded.{{sfn|Henry|2005}} * 1908 ‚Äì [[Seodaemun Prison|Gyeongseong Gamok]] (prison) in operation. * 1910 ** Japanese [[Korea under Japanese rule|in power]]; city renamed "Keij≈ç" ** Population: 200,000 (approximate).{{sfn|Britannica|1910}} * 1914 ‚Äì Outer parts of Gyeongseongbu were ceded to [[Goyang]] County. * 1915 ‚Äì [[Joseon Industrial Exhibition]] held in [[Gyeongbokgung]] * 1920 ‚Äì ''[[Chosun Ilbo]]'' and ''[[Dong-a Ilbo]]'' newspapers begin publication. * 1922 ‚Äì [[Namsan Public Library]] established. * 1924 ‚Äì [[Keij≈ç Imperial University]] founded. * 1925 ‚Äì [[Seoul Station]] opens. * 1926 ‚Äì [[Japanese General Government Building, Seoul|Japanese General Government Building]] constructed. * 1927 ‚Äì [[Noryangjin Fisheries Wholesale Market|Noryangjin Fish Market]] in business.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} * 1936 ‚Äì The expansion of Gyeongseongbu was implemented absorbing Cheongnyangni, Anam, Sincheon, etc. * 1945 ‚Äì [[National Library of Korea]] and [[National Museum of Korea]] established. * 1946 ** City renamed "Seoul" (approximate date).{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} ** Kim Hyongmin becomes mayor. ** [[Seoul National University]] established. * 1947 ‚Äì [[Samsung|Samsung Sanghoe]] in business. * 1948 ** City becomes [[Capital of Korea|capital]] of [[Republic of Korea]]. ** [[Seoul Philharmonic Orchestra]] founded. * 1949 ** Seoul designated a [[Special cities of South Korea|special city]] (administrative division). ** Expended to today's [[Gangbuk-gu]] to the north and Guro-dong, Sindorim-dong(including today's Daerim dong) to the south. ** Population: 1,446,019.<ref>{{cite web |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1950_round.htm |work=Demographic Yearbook 1955 |year= |publisher=[[Statistical Office of the United Nations]] |location=New York |title=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 or more inhabitants }}</ref> * 1950 ** 28 June: [[Hangang Bridge bombing]]; city [[Korean War|taken]] by North Korean army. ** 16 July: [[Yongsan bombing]]. ** 22‚Äì25 September: [[Second Battle of Seoul]]. * 1951 ** January: [[Third Battle of Seoul]]. ** 14 March: City [[Operation Ripper|taken]] by United Nations forces. * 1953 ‚Äì ''[[Korea Herald|Korean Republic]]'' newspaper begins publication. * 1954 ‚Äì ''[[Hankook Ilbo]]'' newspaper begins publication. * 1958 ‚Äì [[Gimpo International Airport]] in operation.
===1960s-1990s=== * 1960 ‚Äì [[Gyeongdong Market]] in business.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} * 1963 ‚Äì The great expansion was implemented, incorporating parts of counties of [[Gimpo]], [[Gwangju]], [[Siheung]], [[Yangju]], and [[Bucheon]]. * 1965 ‚Äì Population: 3,793,280.{{sfn|Yeong-Hyun Kim|2004}} * 1969 ‚Äì [[N Seoul Tower]] built. * 1970 ** [[Gyeongbu Expressway]] constructed. ** Population: 5,433,198.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1970_round.htm |title=Demographic Yearbook 1975 |year=1976 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital city and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=253-279 }}</ref> * 1973 ** Jingwan-dong (Gupabal) was incorporated to Seoul from Goyang County. ** [[Kukkiwon|World Taekwondo Headquarters]] established. * 1974 ** [[Seoul Metropolitan Subway]] begins operating. ** [[Korean Film Archive]] and [[Chugye University for the Arts]] established. * 1975 ‚Äì [[Sister city]] relationship established with [[San Francisco]], USA.<ref>{{cite web |publisher=City & County of San Francisco |title= San Francisco Sister Cities |accessdate=30 December 2015 |url= http://www.oewd.org/index.aspx?page=100 |location=USA }}</ref> * 1977 ‚Äì [[Jeongdok Public Library]] opens. * 1978 ‚Äì [[Sejong Center]] built. * 1980 - Population: 8,364,379.<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1980_round.htm |title=1985 Demographic Yearbook |year=1987 |author=[[United Nations Department of Economic and Social Affairs]], Statistical Office |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=247-289 }}</ref> * 1982 ‚Äì [[Banpo Bridge]] constructed. * 1983 ** [[FC Seoul|Lucky-Goldstar Football Club]] formed. ** [[Bukhansan National Park]] established. * 1985 ** [[63 Building]] constructed. ** Population: 9,639,110.{{sfn|Yeong-Hyun Kim|2004}} * 1986 ‚Äì [[1986 Asian Games|Asian Games]] held. * 1988 ** [[Goh Kun]] becomes mayor. ** [[1988 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] held. ** [[Seoul Museum of Art]] and [[Seoul Arts Center|Calligraphy Museum]] open. ** [[Trade Tower]] built. * 1989 ‚Äì [[Lotte World]] recreation complex opens. * 1990 ‚Äì Population: 10,612,577.{{sfn|Yeong-Hyun Kim|2004}} * 1991 ** [[Blue House]] (government residence) built. ** [[KBS Hall]] opens. * 1993 ** [[Korea National University of Arts]] established. ** [[Seoul Arts Center|Opera House]] opens. ** [[War Memorial of Korea]] constructed. * 1994 ‚Äì [[Hi! Seoul Festival]] begins. * 1995 ** The city boundary between Seoul and [[Gwangmyeong]] was rearranged, absorbing a very tiny part of Cheolsan-dong. ** The city boundary between Seoul and [[Goyang]] was rearranged, absorbing a very tiny part of Jichuk-dong. ** 29 June: [[Sampoong Department Store collapse]].<ref>{{citation |work=[[The Guardian]] |location=UK |year=2015 |url= https://www.theguardian.com/cities/series/history-cities-50-buildings |title= A history of cities in 50 buildings }}</ref> ** Population: 10,776,201 (approximate estimate).<ref>{{cite book |url= https://unstats.un.org/unsd/demographic/products/dyb/1990_round.htm |title=1995 Demographic Yearbook |year=1997 |author=United Nations Department for Economic and Social Information and Policy Analysis, Statistics Division |location=New York |chapter=Population of capital cities and cities of 100,000 and more inhabitants |pages=262-321 }}</ref> * 1999 ‚Äì [[Jongno Tower]] built. * 2000 ** [[Bukchon Hanok Village|Bukchon]] Preservation and Regeneration Project established.{{sfn|Hong|2013}} ** [[Kumho art hall]] opens.{{citation needed|date=February 2013}}
==21st century==
* 2001 ** [[Incheon International Airport]] begins operating. ** [[Seoul World Cup Stadium]] opens. ** [[ETPFEST|ETP music festival]] begins. * 2002 ** [[2002 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]] held. ** [[Lee Myung-bak]] becomes mayor. ** [[Seoul Museum of History]] established. * 2003 - [[Hyperion Tower]] built. * 2004 ** [[Samsung Tower Palace]] built. ** [[Seoul Station]] renovated.{{sfn|Jesook Song|2006}} ** [[Seoul City Amazones|Seoul Metropolitan Government Amazones]] football club formed. * 2005 - [[Seoul Forest]] opens. * 2006 - [[Oh Se-hoon]] becomes mayor. * 2009 ** [[Moonlight Rainbow Fountain]] installed. ** [[West Seoul Lake Park]] opens. * 2010 - November: [[2010 G-20 Seoul summit|G-20 summit]] held. * 2011 ** June: [[2011 Seoul floods|Floods]]. ** October: [[Asian Network of Major Cities 21]] meeting held. ** [[Park Won-soon]] becomes mayor. ** Population: 10,581,728.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.seoul.go.kr/gtk/main.php |title=Get to Know Us |publisher=Seoul Metropolitan Government |accessdate=12 February 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130413143005/http://english.seoul.go.kr/gtk/main.php |archivedate=13 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> ** [[Shinbundang Line]] opens * 2012 ** [[International Finance Center Seoul]] opens ** [[ABU Radio Song Festival 2012|ABU Radio Song Festival]] held. ** [[Seoul City Hall]] rebuilt. * 2014 - [[Dongdaemun Design Plaza]] opens * 2015 - [[Gocheok Sky Dome]] opens * 2016 - March: AI [[AlphaGo versus Lee Sedol]] match played.
