'''Vrbani''' is a [[neighborhood]] in [[Tre≈°njevka - jug]] city district in the southwestern part of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. The area covered by the local city council Vrbani has around 10,093 inhabitants.<ref>http://www.zagreb.hr/default.aspx?id=13552</ref>

The borders of Vrbani are Horvaƒáanska Street on the south with [[Jarun]], Hrvatski Sokol Street with [[Stagli≈°ƒáe]] on the east, [[Zagrebaƒçka Avenue]] with [[Rude≈°]] on the north and Petrovaradinska Street on the west with [[Preƒçko]]. Vrbani, in the wider sense, also includes the newly built buildings between [[lake Jarun]] and Horvaƒáanska Street.

